definition: see 百思不解[bai3 si1 bu4 jie3]
pinyin: bai3 si1 bu4 de2 qi2 jie3

definition: to obtain/to get/to gain/to catch (a disease)/proper/suitable/proud/contented/to allow/to permit/ready/finished
structural particle: used after a verb (or adjective as main verb), linking it to following phrase indicating effect, degree, possibility etc
to have to/must/ought to/to need to
acrobatic display (esp. on horseback) (old)/variant of 懈[xie4] and 邂[xie4] (old)
to divide/to break up/to split/to separate/to dissolve/to solve/to melt/to remove/to untie/to loosen/to open/to emancipate/to explain/to understand/to know/a solution/a dissection

sentences.english: It leaves many nutrition experts scratching their heads. Dr.
sentences.chinese: 这种断食法让许多营养专家百思不得其解。

sentences.english: All this might have you scratching your head.
sentences.chinese: 所有这一切可能会让你百思不得其解。

sentences.english: That is the question many biotechnologists in America have recently asked themselves.
sentences.chinese: 这正是让生物技术学家百思不得其解的问题。

sentences.english: Zhang thought that the mattress hundred think do not its solution.
sentences.chinese: 张先生觉褥百思不得其解。

sentences.english: The hat was in place and tied, but Tess had not stepped forward.
sentences.chinese: 是时间的反噬？还是命运的岔道？陈暮百思不得其解。

definition: to remain puzzled after pondering over sth a hundred times (idiom)/to remain perplexed despite much thought
unable to understand/unable to get over
to not understand/to be puzzled by/indissoluble
